Introduction

Shin Suhyun is a South Korean actress and model under Management Run.

In 2017, Shin Suhyun was a contestant on JTBC and YG Entertainment' survival show MIXNINE. She was sadly eliminated in episode 7 after ranking 59th.

In 2018, she competed in MNET's hit survival show Produce 48 where she ranked 61th place and was eliminated in episode 8.

During her participation on both survivals, Shin Suhyun was signed with FAVE Entertainment. She took part in the agency pre-debut group FAVE GIRLS (now known as Weeekly), but left both of them some times in 2018 and signed with SUBLIME.

From 2019 to 2021, she appeared in various music videos such as "Snowflakes" by Ovan and Vinxen, and "Side by Side" by The8.

Shin Suhyun made her acting debut as a supporting role in the drama "Woman of 9.9 Billion", which aired from December 2019 to January 2020. Since then, she got roles in dramas such as "At a Distance, Spring Is Green", which aired in 2021, "Duty After School" in 2023, and "Study Group", in 2025.

On December 11, 2020, she won the "Best New Actor/Actress" award at the 2020 Grimae Awards for her role in the drama "Woman of 9.9 Billion".

On January 14, 2024, Management Run announced on Instagram that Shin Suhyun joined their agency, implying that she had left SUBLIME.
